<rdf:Description rdf:about="http://data.europa.eu/c4p/data/c_48_it">
	<rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept"/>
	<hasBiasCategory xmlns="http://data.europa.eu/c4p/ontology#" rdf:resource="http://data.europa.eu/c4p/data/cat_11"/>
	<hasContentiousTerm xmlns="http://data.europa.eu/c4p/ontology#" rdf:resource="http://data.europa.eu/c4p/data/t_68_it"/>
	<description xmlns="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xml:lang="it">Termine di origine provenzale “bagassa” e francese “baiasse” e/o “bagasse” col significato di «servente» e/o «fanciulla». Il termine e' usato in modo offensivo col significato di “prostituta“.</description>
	<source xmlns="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xml:lang="en">“Bagàscia,” in Treccani, n.d., accessed April 3, 2024, https://www.treccani.it/vocabolario/bagascia/.</source>
	<title xmlns="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xml:lang="it">Bagascia</title>
